---
import Default from "../layouts/Default.astro";
---

<Default title="About" description="About QueryGym — the team and motivation behind an open-source toolkit for reproducible LLM-based query reformulation in information retrieval research.">
  <section class="qg-section !py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl">About</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-qg-fg-muted">
      QueryGym is built by the <strong>LS3 Lab</strong> with collaborators
      across the IR community. The aim is to make LLM-based query reformulation
      research <em>easy to reproduce</em>: same prompt bank, same data shape,
      same retrieval contracts, regardless of which LLM, dataset, or method
      you're benchmarking.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl font-semibold">Authors</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-qg-fg-muted">
      Amin Bigdeli · Radin Hamidi Rad · Mert Incesu · Negar Arabzadeh ·
      Charles L. A. Clarke · Ebrahim Bagheri
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl font-semibold">License</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-qg-fg-muted">
      Apache 2.0. Free to use commercially. Schema and reproducibility
      artifacts are in the public domain (CC0).
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl font-semibold">Contributing</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-qg-fg-muted">
      New methods, datasets, and reproducibility runs are welcome. See the
      <a class="text-qg-accent hover:underline" href="https://querygym.readthedocs.io/en/latest/development/contributing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        contributor guide
      </a>
      and the
      <a class="text-qg-accent hover:underline" href="/reproducibility">
        reproducibility flow
      </a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</Default>
